  "dailyScripture0Text": "Indeed, the righteous will be among gardens and rivers, in a seat of honor near a Mighty King.",
  "dailyScripture0Ref": "Quran 54:54-55",
  "dailyScripture1Text": "And We have not sent you, [O Muhammad], except as a mercy to the worlds.",
  "dailyScripture1Ref": "Quran 21:107",
  "dailyScripture2Text": "Is not Allah sufficient for His servant? Yet they frighten you with others besides Him.",
  "dailyScripture2Ref": "Quran 39:36",
  "dailyScripture3Text": "Perhaps you hate something and it is good for you; and perhaps you love something and it is bad for you. And Allah knows, while you know not.",
  "dailyScripture3Ref": "Quran 2:216",
  "dailyScripture4Text": "Indeed, Allah is with the patient ones.",
  "dailyScripture4Ref": "Quran 2:153",
  "dailyScripture5Text": "So remember Me; I will remember you. And be grateful to Me and do not deny Me.",
  "dailyScripture5Ref": "Quran 2:152",
  "dailyScripture6Text": "Indeed, the most noble of you in the sight of Allah is the most righteous of you.",
  "dailyScripture6Ref": "Quran 49:13",
  "dailyScripture7Text": "And your Lord has decreed that you worship none but Him, and that you be dutiful to your parents.",
  "dailyScripture7Ref": "Quran 17:23",
  "dailyScripture8Text": "Verily, with hardship comes ease.",
  "dailyScripture8Ref": "Quran 94:6",
  "dailyScripture9Text": "And He is with you wherever you are. And Allah, of what you do, is Seeing.",
  "dailyScripture9Ref": "Quran 57:4",
  "dailyScripture10Text": "Allah does not burden a soul beyond that it can bear.",
  "dailyScripture10Ref": "Quran 2:286",
  "dailyScripture11Text": "And whoever relies upon Allah — then He is sufficient for him.",
  "dailyScripture11Ref": "Quran 65:3",
  "dailyScripture12Text": "My mercy encompasses all things.",
  "dailyScripture12Ref": "Quran 7:156",
  "dailyScripture13Text": "And when My servants ask you about Me — indeed I am near. I respond to the supplicant when he calls upon Me.",
  "dailyScripture13Ref": "Quran 2:186",
  "dailyScripture14Text": "Whoever does righteousness, whether male or female, while being a believer — We will surely cause him to live a good life.",
  "dailyScripture14Ref": "Quran 16:97",
  "dailyScripture15Text": "Indeed, Allah will not change the condition of a people until they change what is in themselves.",
  "dailyScripture15Ref": "Quran 13:11",
  "dailyScripture16Text": "So do not weaken and do not grieve, and you will be superior if you are true believers.",
  "dailyScripture16Ref": "Quran 3:139",
  "dailyScripture17Text": "O My servants who have transgressed against themselves, do not despair of the mercy of Allah. Indeed, Allah forgives all sins.",
  "dailyScripture17Ref": "Quran 39:53",
  "dailyScripture18Text": "And whoever fears Allah — He will make for him a way out, and will provide for him from where he does not expect.",
  "dailyScripture18Ref": "Quran 65:2-3",
  "dailyScripture19Text": "Do not lose hope in the mercy of Allah.",
  "dailyScripture19Ref": "Quran 12:87",
  "dailyScripture20Text": "And We have certainly made the Quran easy to remember. So is there anyone who will be mindful?",
  "dailyScripture20Ref": "Quran 54:17",
  "dailyScripture21Text": "And He found you lost and guided you.",
  "dailyScripture21Ref": "Quran 93:7",
  "dailyScripture22Text": "And your Lord says: Call upon Me; I will respond to you.",
  "dailyScripture22Ref": "Quran 40:60",
  "dailyScripture23Text": "And We have certainly honored the children of Adam.",
  "dailyScripture23Ref": "Quran 17:70",
  "dailyScripture24Text": "And seek help through patience and prayer.",
  "dailyScripture24Ref": "Quran 2:45",
  "dailyScripture25Text": "Whoever does an atom's weight of good will see it.",
  "dailyScripture25Ref": "Quran 99:7",
  "dailyScripture26Text": "Unquestionably, the help of Allah is near.",
  "dailyScripture26Ref": "Quran 2:214",
  "dailyScripture27Text": "And whoever is grateful — his gratitude is only for the benefit of himself.",
  "dailyScripture27Ref": "Quran 31:12",

  "dailyReflection0": "As this day closes, consider one moment where Allah's mercy was evident.",
  "dailyReflection1": "Bring before Allah whatever weighed on your heart today.",
  "dailyReflection2": "Name one blessing from this day and express gratitude to Allah.",
  "dailyReflection3": "Rest in the knowledge that you are held in Allah's infinite care.",
  "dailyReflection4": "Reflect on where you felt called to show compassion and kindness today.",
  "dailyReflection5": "Let go of what you cannot control and trust in Allah's perfect plan.",
  "dailyReflection6": "As the day draws to a close, receive peace in remembrance of Allah.",
  "dailyReflection7": "Consider how you honored your prayers today, and thank Allah for each one.",
  "dailyReflection8": "Reflect on a moment where patience (Sabr) guided your actions today.",
  "dailyReflection9": "Ask forgiveness for any shortcoming today — Allah's mercy is boundless.",
  "dailyReflection10": "Name one person you showed kindness to today and make dua for them.",
  "dailyReflection11": "Sit with gratitude: what did Allah provide today that you did not ask for?",
  "dailyReflection12": "Reflect on a verse from the Quran that speaks to where you are right now.",
  "dailyReflection13": "Consider how you used your time today — and offer tomorrow to Allah.",
  "dailyReflection14": "Rest knowing that whatever hardship came today, Allah was with you through it.",
  "dailyReflection15": "Think of one way you served your family or community today for Allah's sake.",
  "dailyReflection16": "As night falls, make Tawbah — Allah loves those who turn back to Him.",
  "dailyReflection17": "Reflect on the beauty Allah placed in your day, however small.",
  "dailyReflection18": "Consider what you learned today and how it draws you closer to Allah.",
  "dailyReflection19": "Let the day's worries rest with Allah — He carries what you cannot.",
  "dailyReflection20": "Think of a moment today where you could have chosen better, and learn from it gently.",
  "dailyReflection21": "Make dua for those who are struggling — your prayer is a gift to them.",
  "dailyReflection22": "Recall a blessing you often overlook and take a moment to thank Allah for it.",
  "dailyReflection23": "Reflect on your intentions today — were they for Allah? Tomorrow, begin again.",
  "dailyReflection24": "As the night quiets, listen for Allah's nearness in the stillness.",
  "dailyReflection25": "Consider where you found strength today — that strength is from Allah.",
  "dailyReflection26": "Name one thing you will do tomorrow, for Allah's sake, that you did not do today.",
  "dailyReflection27": "As you prepare for rest, entrust your soul to Allah — He is the best of guardians.",

